# Working drafts — not for repo
_temp/*
!_temp/.gitkeep

# User layer — personal config, memory, feedback. Never committed, never touched by /os-update.
# (CLAUDE.md itself is template-only since OS 1.1.0 and is safe to track.)
Users/*
!Users/README.md
!Users/_template/
!Users/_template/**

# Review verdict files (generated by pre-publish gates)
*.riddler-passed
*.vicki-passed

# WhatsApp Web cache (not part of the OS)
.wwebjs_cache/

# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Editor
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# User-owned working files — tracked as blank templates, personalized after onboarding.
# The template freezes these upstream; /os-update keeps your local version on conflict.
# Uncomment ONLY if you've personalised the OS and plan to push a sanitised fork:
#
# GOALS.md            ← contains your personal goals
# Tasks/active.md     ← contains your real tasks
# Tasks/backlog.md
# Tasks/follow-ups.md
# Knowledge/People/   ← contains stakeholder profiles
# Projects/           ← contains real campaign briefs

# Verdict files (generated artifacts — optional to commit)
# *.brief-review-passed
# *.campaign-readiness-passed
# *.experiment-readiness-passed

# Lark wiki index files — these are populated per-user after onboarding.
# Uncomment to prevent committing your team's internal wiki data:
# Knowledge/Reference/lark-wiki-index.md
# Knowledge/Reference/lark-wiki-performance-marketing.md
